HEADWORD: maidenhair tree
<hw>maidenhair tree</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A deciduous dioecious
gymnospermous Chinese tree (<spn>Ginkgo biloba</spn>) having fan-shaped
leaves and fleshy yellow seeds, also called the
<altname>ginkgo</altname>; it exists almost exclusively in cultivation
esp. as an ornamental street tree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maidenhead</ent>⟦br⟧
